#Text=Anna Leuhusen
#Text=St. Clare 's Priory , Stockholm Blodbadsplanschen 1524
#Text=Anna Rheinholdsdotter Leuhusen ( died c. 1554 ) , was the Abbess of St. Clare 's Priory in Stockholm .
#Text=She became known for her involvement in the Swedish War of Liberation between Sweden and Denmark in the 1520s .
#Text=Background

#Text=Anna Leuhusen was born the child of Reinhold Leuhusen , merchant in Stockholm , and the sister of Martin Leuhusen , who is listed as a member of the city council of 1521 ; Martin Leuhusen was a fervent Catholic who did not convert until 1536 .
#Text=Her sister was married to the Danish colonel Gregorius Holst .
#Text=The year of her birth is unknown .
#Text=Anna Lehusen entered the Clara Abbey as a member of the order of Saint Clare of Assisi .
#Text=She was appointed abbess sometime prior to 1508 .
#Text=This year , she is confirmed as such , when she appealed to the city for economic assistance in her capacity of abbess .
#Text=Act during the war
#Text=During this period , Sweden and Denmark , formally united through the Kalmar Union , was involved in various warfare which eventually led to the Swedish War of Liberation .
#Text=In 1520 , the city of Stockholm was sieged and taken by the Danes after the defeat of Christina Gyllenstierna .
#Text=Soon after , however , the rest of Sweden rose in rebellion and in 1522 , the city was besieged by the Swedes under Gustav Vasa .
#Text=During the siege , the St. Clare 's Priory was used as an escape channel by people who wished to join the Swedes outside the city , both merchants and courtiers .
#Text=Leuhusen was a Danish loyalist and , according to the legend , responsible for betraying several of these people .

#Text=During the day , she signaled by hanging a white cloth out of the window and , during the night , a lamp to the part of the convent facing the city , as a sign to the Danes that there were refugees in the building .
#Text=When they left the convent on their way outside the city , they were taken by the Danes and executed for treason .
#Text=This was performed in collaboration with her brother-in-law , the Danish loyalist mayor of Stockholm . [ 1 ]
#Text=Later life
#Text=In June 1523 , Stockholm was retaken by the Swedes and made capital of the independent Kingdom of Sweden .
#Text=In 1525 , Elin Thomasdotter is noted to have replaced Anna Leuhusen as abbess .
#Text=The St. Clare 's Priory was to be one of the very first convents to be dissolved during the Swedish Reformation in 1527 .
#Text=This has been contributed to the acts of Anna Leuhusen during the war , for which the King felt vengeful . [ 2 ]

#Text=Former Abbess Anna Leuhusen and the rest of the nuns was allowed to settle in the dissolved Grey Friar Abbey , which had been left empty by the monks , where they worked as nurses the rest of their lives .
#Text=Anna Leuhusen is known to have kept one of the convent most treasured possessions .
#Text=When the abbey was founded in 1288 , Princess Richenza of Sweden had entered it , and became its abbess in 1335 .
#Text=Richenza possessed a golden chain , which was consequently used by the abbesses of the abbey for centuries .
#Text=Anna Leuhusen kept this chain when the abbey was dissolved and gave it to her family .
#Text=Anna Leuhusen was still alive in 1550 .
#Text=She is believed to have died around 1554 .
